The '''2012 [[Indian Premier League]]''' season, abbreviated as '''IPL 5''' or the '''IPL 2012''', will be the fifth season of the Indian Premier League, established by the [[Board of Control for Cricket in India]] (BCCI) in 2007. While [[Chennai Super Kings]] will compete as defending champions, [[Chepauk]], their home venue, is expected to host the finals. The tournament will begin on [[April 4]] and end [[May 27]] [[2012]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/india/content/current/story/520912.html |title=IPL 2012 from April 4 to May 27 |date=2011-06-27 |publisher=[[CricInfo]]|accessdate=2011-06-27 }}</ref>
==Kochi's Termination== The IPL Committee has terminated the IPL franchise [[Kochi Tuskers Kerala]]. Despite KTK's efforts, the court haven't given them any relief and the IPL Governing Council decided that the tournament be reduced to 9 teams. However, KTK players will participate in IPL 2012.The auction will be held for KTK players and other players on 19th February 2012.
==Format==
==Points System== The winning team gets 2 points, losing 0 and in case of No result both team gets 1-1 point each. In case of a tie, the match will be decided by a [[Super Over]].
